verbose_text: The H4 acetylation of the FoxO3a promoter region was markedly decreased in the H 2 O 2 -exposed cells compared with that of the control group (p < 0.01), whereas TSA elicited a significant increase in H4 acetylation of the FoxO3a promoter region compared with that of the H 2 O 2 group.
